                  <msItem>
                     <p>.
                         
                        <persName>Master <forename>Robert</forename> of <surname>Rypplingham</surname>, chancellor of the church of <placeName role="person" key="place_103421">York</placeName>
                        </persName>, has received the church of <placeName key="place_108047">Preston-in-Craven</placeName> from <orgName key="org_103008">Boulton</orgName> for 3 years from Midsummer, 1317, for a certain sum of money. He has granted it for the same term to <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Geyregrave</surname>, vicar of <placeName role="vicar" key="place_107097">Kyldewyk</placeName>
                        </persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> de <surname>Herdeslawe</surname>, vicar of <placeName role="vicar" key="place_103347">Skypton</placeName>
                        </persName>, and <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> vicar of <placeName role="vicar" key="place_107098">Carletone</placeName>
                        </persName>, for 360 marks. The monks have constituted themselves principal debtors for this sum, of which he has received 100 marks, owed them 50 marks, has pardoned 120 marks, and is to receive 80 marks.
                        Given at <placeName role="date" key="place_103029">York</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1319-11-03">
                           <supplied>3 Nov.</supplied> 1319.</origDate>
                    </p>
